      'Verify clear title through chain of title analysis going back decades. Identify all encumbrances, liens, mortgages, and charges. Map all pending and potential litigation. Verify RERA registration status. Confirm environmental clearances, building plan approvals, and zoning compliance.',
      'Technical and Construction Assessment',
      'Evaluate structural integrity with independent engineers. Assess work completed versus remaining. Examine quality of materials and construction methods. Check existing MEP systems. Develop a detailed cost-to-complete estimate. For projects stalled for years, structural degradation can significantly increase completion costs.',
      'The model must account for acquisition cost, cost to complete, holding costs (interest, taxes, insurance, security), marketing and sales costs, and expected sale prices. Stress-test for construction delays, cost overruns, and lower sale prices. A well-structured deal maintains margin of safety under adverse assumptions.',
